Privacy Policy
In this Privacy Policy, the terms "we", "us", "the games", "our games", "the apps", "our apps" or "the Applications" refer to Solitaire Card Studio.
We ("us", "we", "the games", "our games", "the apps", "our apps" or "the Applications") recognize that privacy is significant. This Privacy Policy applies to your use of our games.
We ("us", "we", "the games", "our games", "the apps", "our apps" or "the Applications") have created this Policy to explain our privacy practices so that you will understand what information about you is collected, used and disclosed with respect to the games.
By using the games, you consent to the privacy practices described in this Policy.
This Policy covers our collection, use and disclosure of your information through the games. It does not cover any collection, use or disclosure by third parties through the games that we do not control or own, such as Facebook, or
            any third party features or services made available via the games. All trademarks, trade names, and logos of third parties featured on the games belong to their respective owners.
A. WHAT KIND OF INFORMATION WE COLLECT
We collect the following information:
1. The system language;
2. The MCC;
3. The version code;
4. The version name;
5. The Unity version;
6. The OS (iOS or Android);
7. The OS version;
8. The device name;
9. The device memory;
10. The screen resolution;
11. The device model;
12. The IP address;
13. The Advertising tracking ID (Identifier for Advertising (IDFA) on iOS, Google Advertising ID on Android), you can reset or erased at any time in your device settings;
14. The email address when you send us feedback with email address filled;
15. The country code;
16. The actions you do in the games, for example, open an page.
B. WHY WE COLLECT AND HOW WE USE COLLECTED INFORMATION
We may use the information for the following purpose:
1. To understand demographics of our users, and improve user experience;
2. To communicate with you when you send us feedback with email address filled;
3. To fix the crash and ANR issues on some special devices;
4. To construct the attribution links of third Party Ads. Currently we construct attribution link for Unity Ads, Unity will protect your privacy strictly as described in their privacy policy, see more
https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy
.
C. INFORMATION MAY BE SHARED with THIRD-PARTY
We use THIRD-PARTY Ads to enable us to offer our app for free. We use THIRD-PARTY to help us to analyze data and they will collect the related data by themselves by their SDKs after your consent. The details are listed below:
1. We use Facebook ads, the related privacy policy is described by Facebook, see more details in
https://m.facebook.com/ads/ad_choices
2. We use Admob ads and Firebase, the related privacy policy is described by Google, see more details in
https://policies.google.com/privacy
